# Knowledge Base Conventions

This file is read by Claude at the start of every knowledge skill invocation.
Do not delete it. Edit it as your knowledge base evolves.

---

## Directory Structure

```
~/knowledge/
├── raw/          # Source material inbox — LLM reads but rarely edits these
│   ├── articles/ # Web articles, blog posts (YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md)
│   ├── papers/   # PDFs or transcripts of research papers
│   └── images/   # Screenshots, diagrams
├── wiki/         # LLM-compiled knowledge — do not edit manually
│   ├── _index.md # Master index (one line per article)
│   ├── _meta/    # Lint reports and health metadata
│   └── <topic>/  # One directory per concept cluster
└── outputs/      # Rendered deliverables
    ├── reports/  # Q&A outputs (YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md)
    └── slides/   # Marp slideshows
```

---

## Front Matter Fields

Every file in `raw/` must have YAML front matter:

```yaml
---
title: "Article Title"
source: "https://original-url.com"
date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
tags: [tag1, tag2]
status: unprocessed   # unprocessed | compiled | stub | draft | complete
---
```

Every file in `wiki/` must have YAML front matter:

```yaml
---
title: "Concept Name"
tags: [tag1, tag2]
status: complete      # stub | draft | complete
sources:
  - raw/articles/YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md
---
```

---

## `_index.md` Format

One line per wiki article, kept sorted by topic:

```
- [[topic/concept]] — One-sentence summary of what this article covers. (source: raw/articles/slug.md)
```

The `_index.md` is the LLM's map of the entire wiki. Keep it accurate and complete.
Every wiki article must have exactly one entry here. Orphans and missing entries are lint errors.

---

## Wikilink Format

Use Obsidian `[[wikilink]]` syntax for all internal links (not markdown href syntax).
This enables Obsidian's graph view and backlink detection.

- Link to a concept: `[[topic/concept]]`
- Link with display text: `[[topic/concept|display text]]`

Every article must have a `## See Also` section at the bottom with wikilinks to related concepts.

---

## Topic Directory Naming

- Lowercase, hyphenated: `machine-learning`, `distributed-systems`, `product-design`
- Broad concept clusters — prefer fewer, broader topics over many narrow ones
- Each topic directory has an `index.md` summarising the topic and listing all articles in it

---

## Article Length & Style

- Target: under 500 words per article unless the concept genuinely requires more
- Write in present tense, encyclopedic style
- Lead with a one-sentence definition of the concept
- Never delete content — archive superseded sections with `> [Archived: YYYY-MM-DD]`

---

## Compile Behaviour

When a raw document spans multiple topics:
1. Create one **primary** article in the most relevant topic directory
2. Add `## See Also` wikilinks from related topic articles pointing to the primary
3. Do not duplicate content across articles — cross-link instead

When updating an existing wiki article with new information from a raw doc:
1. Merge new information into the existing article
2. Add the new source to the article's `sources:` front matter list
3. Update the one-line summary in `_index.md` if it has changed

---

## PDF Workflow (if applicable)

If PDFs become a significant source type, consider Zotero + Zotero2MD plugin to export
highlights and annotations as structured markdown into `raw/papers/`. See the plan at
`~/dev/agentic-home/plans/knowledge-base.md` for details.
